Requirements:
Java installed version 11 or later 
https://www.oracle.com/technetwork/java/javase/downloads/index.html

Sample command to run:
C:\java\jdk-11.0.3\bin\java.exe -jar poopClear.jar

PoopClear help solve some common transformations issues.

1) bad for-each mappings generated by jdev automap.
  PoopClear will help to find and automatically correct these mappings, just select the file you want to analyze.

2) search logic points in transformation.
  PoopClear will help to find uncommon mappings, you can select a directory and a report will be generated with each file and the line with uncommon mappings founded
